%20continuity.%20Likewise%2C%20there%20is%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fthe-world-24x7%2Fwhy-is-west-asia-epicentre-of-power-play-between-america-china-and-russia-777564%5C%22%3ERussia-Iran-China%3C%2Fa%3E%20axis%20based%20on%20common%20interests%20and%20grievances%20with%20the%20West.%20But%20there%20are%20limits%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20support%20that%20each%20lends%20to%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20mutual%20antagonism%2C%20Israel%20and%20Iran%20now%20appear%20to%20be%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20new%20conflict.%20The%20proximate%20cause%20for%20this%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20Israel's%20frustration%20with%20what%20it%20argues%20is%20Iranian%20support%20for%20Hamas%2C%20and%20other%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhezbollah-says-3-fighters-killed-in-israel-strike-in-southern-lebanon-5487566%5C%22%3EHezbollah%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Houthis%2C%20the%20Syrian%20government%20and%20groups%20in%20Iraq.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20past%20month%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20engaged%20in%20a%20cycle%20of%20attack%20and%20counter-attack.%20Neither%20seems%20to%20desire%20a%20major%20escalation.%20But%20the%20ladder%20of%20escalation%20often%20follows%20its%20own%20logic%2C%20which%20can%20put%20the%20best-laid%20plans%20to%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3ETwo%20Planks%20Of%20Power%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20strategic%20outcomes%20can%20be%20observed%20amid%20these%20recent%20events.%20First%2C%20the%20persistence%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20emerging%20spillovers%20have%20exposed%20the%20limitations%20of%20American%20and%20Chinese%20power%2C%20particularly%20since%20the%20situation%20does%20not%20necessarily%20serve%20either's%20strategic%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20alignment%2C%20albeit%20with%20increasing%20friction%2C%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Israel.%20The%20US%20has%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%2C%20supporting%20Israel%20in%20its%20war%20against%20Hamas%2C%20and%20led%20its%20defence%20amid%20the%20recent%20Iranian%20strikes.%20It%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20this%20effort%20was%20supported%20by%20regional%20actors%20like%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20UAE%20and%20Jordan.%20In%20addition%2C%20options%20to%20coerce%20Iran%20economically%20are%20being%20discussed%20in%20both%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%20and%20the%20US.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20China%20and%20Russia%20have%20been%20critical%20of%20Israeli%20actions%20since%20October%202023.%20Amid%20the%20Iran-Israel%20tensions%2C%20Beijing%20has%20backed%20Iran%20and%20sought%20to%20preserve%20its%20tenuous%20effort%20at%20reconciliation%20between%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Tehran.%20Russia%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20become%20Iran's%20largest%20military%20backer%20since%202022%20and%20threw%20its%20diplomatic%20weight%20behind%20Iran's%20%26quot%3Bretaliatory%20measures%26quot%3B%20on%20April%2014%20against%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia%20More%20Dependent%20Than%20Ever%20On%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20world%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20well%20into%20its%20third%20year.%20The%20conflict%20has%20fundamentally%20reshaped%20European%20geopolitics%20and%20geoeconomics.%20The%20war%20has%20re-energised%20transatlantic%20unity%20for%20the%20moment.%20However%2C%20the%20direction%20of%20American%20domestic%20politics%20has%20a%20significant%20bearing%20on%20this%20momentum.%20Beijing%20has%20sought%20to%20straddle%20the%20line%20in%20Europe%20by%20trying%20to%20appear%20neutral%20while%20backing%20the%20Russian%20call%20for%20a%20new%20regional%20security%20architecture.%20It%20has%20supported%20Russia's%20defence%20industrial%20complex%20with%20the%20supply%20of%20dual-use%20items%2C%20but%20has%20been%20cautious%20to%20avoid%20direct%20weapons%20support.%20Russia%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20economically%20become%20more%20dependent%20than%20ever%20on%20China.%20It%20views%20China%20as%20indispensable%20in%20shaping%20a%20new%20global%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20visit%20by%20Russian%20Foreign%20Minister%20Sergei%20Lavrov%20to%20China%20underscored%20the%20strategic%20nature%20of%20the%20relationship.%20Chinese%20Foreign%20Minister%20Wang%20Yi%20was%20blunt%20in%20stating%20that%20their%20ties%20were%20%26quot%3Birreplaceable%20in%20maintaining%20global%20strategic%20stability%20and%20promoting%20cooperation%20among%20emerging%20powers%26quot%3B.%20Both%20men%20condemned%20the%20US%20for%20creating%20%26quot%3Bclosed%20military-political%20alliances%20%5Blike%20NATO%5D%20with%20a%20limited%20set%20of%20members%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20expressed%20willingness%20to%20create%20alternative%20institutions%20where%20China%20and%20Russia%20can%20shape%20norms%20in%20a%20way%20that%20suits%20their%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran's%20Quid%20Pro%20Quo%20Approach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%2C%20too%2C%20has%20played%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20role%20in%20supporting%20Russia%20in%20its%20war%20against%20Ukraine%2C%20both%20diplomatically%20and%20militarily.%20In%20fact%2C%20as%20per%20a%20recent%20US%20Congress%20report%2C%20Iran%20not%20only%20maintains%20a%20steady%20supply%20of%20drones%2C%20air-to-ground%20munitions%2C%20and%20artillery%20ammunition%20to%20Russia%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%20building%20a%20drone%20production%20factory%20inside%20Russian%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20Russia%2C%20China%20and%20Iran%20are%20increasingly%20deepening%20cooperation%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%20In%20March%2C%20they%20held%20the%20fourth%20edition%20of%20their%20annual%20trilateral%20naval%20exercises%20in%20the%20northern%20Indian%20Ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETricky%20Landscape%20For%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cascade%20of%20conflicts%20obviously%20has%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20India's%20external%20environment.%20A%20more%20volatile%20world%20makes%20pursuing%20development%20security%20all%20the%20more%20challenging.%20Within%20this%20context%2C%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20strong%20partnership%20between%20China%2C%20Russia%20and%20Iran%2C%20founded%20on%20an%20anti-Western%20sentiment%2C%20has%20serious%20implications%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20efforts%20by%20the%20three%20countries%20to%20shape%20norms%20across%20the%20Global%20South%20and%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20or%20at%20institutions%20such%20as%20the%20BRICS%20and%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperation%20Organization%2C%20could%20chip%20away%20at%20India's%20strategic%20space.%20This%20is%20particularly%20the%20case%20given%20India's%20democratic%20values%2C%20deepening%20ties%20with%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%2C%20and%20its%20strategic%20competition%20with%20China.%20Moreover%2C%20their%20closer%20military%20cooperation%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20portends%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20Cold%20War-style%20camp%20confrontation.%20This%20is%20detrimental%20to%20India's%20approach%20of%20multi-alignment%20and%20maintaining%20strategic%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Manoj%20Kewalramani%20is%20the%20Chairperson%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20Studies%20Programme%20at%20the%20Takshashila%20Institution.%20Anushka%20Saxena%20is%20a%20Research%20Analyst%20with%20Takshashila's%20Indo-Pacific%20Studies%20Programme.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20authors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713764160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F4mosj49_iran-afp-_625x300_19_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Firan-israel-faceoff-why-india-may-find-it-hard-to-navigate-emerging-russia-china-iran-axis-5494559%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20may%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20balance%20it