%20trends%2C%20Nick%20Shah%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Shah%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fcompany%2Fpeterson-technology-partners%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeterson%20Technology%20Partners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2026-year-old%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etech%20staffing%20agency%20based%20in%20Park%20Ridge%2C%20Illinois.%20A%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20placed%20over%20300%20people%20in%20the%20past%20year%20and%20screens%20about%201%2C000%20candidates%20monthly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShah%20shared%20three%20other%20ways%20candidates%20can%20optimize%20LinkedIn%20to%20stand%20out%20to%20hiring%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Treat%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20like%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20used%20to%20enhancing%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20to%20stand%20out%20in%20employers'%20keyword-searching%20software.%20Add%20those%20phrases%20to%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20too%2C%20because%20recruiters%20look%20for%20candidates%20by%20typing%20in%20industry-related%20keywords%2C%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCandidates%20should%20include%20relevant%20keywords%20in%20the%20'About'%20section%20and%20their%20last%20job%20experience%20position%20details%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20place%20is%20considered%20off-limits%20for%20keywords.%20If%20you%20can%20get%20a%20recruiter's%20attention%20with%20the%20right%20skills%20mentioned%20in%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20and%20back%20it%20up%20with%20technical%20expertise%2C%20you%20are%20doing%20it%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20one%20of%20his%20recruiters%20found%20a%20security%20architect%20who%2C%20in%20his%20title%2C%20described%20his%20background%20in%20cloud%20security%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20and%20specified%20his%20certifications.%20In%20his%20skills%20section%2C%20he%20listed%20his%20focus%20within%20cybersecurity%20and%20his%20Microsoft%20Office%20and%20cloud%20proficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShah%20said%20these%20keywords%20helped%20the%20recruiter%20spot%20that%20the%20candidate%20was%20a%20right%20fit%20for%20the%20client%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he'll%20likely%20receive%20an%20offer%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Use%20it%20for%20healthy%20comparisons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20is%20a%20library%20of%20professional%20profiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20your%20profile%20stand%20out%20and%20get%20noticed%20by%20recruiters%2C%20it%20can%20be%20helpful%20to%20compare%20it%20to%20profiles%20of%20people%20working%20at%20companies%20you%20admire%2C%26quot%3B%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20comparing%20their%20LinkedIn%20page%20to%20yours%2C%20you%20can%20find%20gaps%20in%20your%20own%20profile%20information%20and%20skills%20you%20might%20consider%20developing%2C%20Shah%20said.%20Keep%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20your%20work%20experiences%20section%2C%20which%20should%20include%20clear%20and%20succinct%20examples%20of%20your%20work%2C%20and%20result%20metrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Make%20yourself%20visible%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegularly%20share%20content%20and%20engage%20with%20posts%20from%20your%20network.%20This%20engagement%20increases%20your%20chances%20of%20being%20spotted%20by%20recruiters%20and%20hiring%20managers%2C%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECandidates%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-post-an-article-on-linkedin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20articles%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20platform%20or%20contribute%20to%20the%20newer%20%26quot%3Bcollaborative%20article%26quot%3B%20tool%2C%20which%20allows%20users%20to%20share%20under%20a%20LinkedIn-created%20prompt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-linkedin-to-find-new-job-keywords-comparison-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Inside