2C%20anthropology%2C%20economics%20to%20symbolic%20logic%20apart%20from%20traditional%20subjects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20undergraduate%20degree%2C%20she%20worked%20at%20Accenture%20in%20Chicago%2C%20Singapore%2C%20Sydney%2C%20and%20then%20back%20again%20in%20the%20US%20in%20San%20Francisco%20in%20financial%20services%2C%20technology%20and%20consulting%20for%20almost%2019%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20work%20also%20brought%20her%20to%20India%20almost%2010%20years%20later%2C%20in%20the%20post%20liberalisation%20era.%20For%20someone%20working%20in%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20found%20a%20stark%20difference%20and%20a%20big%20gap%20in%20accessibility%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20filled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20then%20decided%20to%20spend%20her%20weekends%20every%20summer%20as%20a%20social%20impact%20business%20mentor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20would%20spend%20time%20with%20entrepreneurs%20across%20the%20world%2C%20including%20India%2C%20and%20help%20them%20develop%20their%20business%20ideas%2C%20models%20and%20also%20face%20related%20challenges%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20followed%20this%20mentorship%20up%20with%20an%20executive%20MBA%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20Haas%20School%20of%20Business.%20She%20noticed%20a%20pattern%20in%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20people%20in%20India%2C%20and%20one%20recurring%20challenge%20emerged%20%E2%80%94%20access%20to%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFinding%20the%20missing%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20spent%20three%20months%20in%20India%20with%20bankers%2C%20techies%2C%20and%20self-help%20groups%20to%20understand%20where%20the%20gap%20in%20access%20to%20capital%20lay%20before%20starting%20Kinara.%20After%20all%2C%20micro%20finance%20and%20Non-Banking%20Financial%20Companies%20(NBFCs)%20had%20expanded%20very%20well%20in%20the%20country%20by%20then%2C